CAPITOL MILLING COMPANY, Appellant, v. Nat ROGAN, as Collector, etc., Appellee. No. 8545. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 14, 1937. Loeb, Walker & Loeb and Herman F. Selvin, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Peirson • M. Hall, U. S. Atty., of Los 'Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, . GARRECHT, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel, ordered appeal dismissed; decree of dismissal filed and entered accordingly; mandate issued forthwith.
